@plane z=3 label="Practical Layer"
# Logistics & Numbers

## Getting Around
| Mode | Cost | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Metro single | €1.61 | Buy Viva Viagem card (€0.50) first |
| Tram 28 | €3.10 | Tourist trap — skip it |
| Tram 15E | €3.10 | Actually useful for Belém |
| Uber/Bolt | €4–12 | Fine outside rush hour |
| Walking | free | Default mode for all 3 days |

## Budget Per Day (mid-range)
- Accommodation: €80–130 (Bairro Alto or Mouraria area)
- Food: €35–55 (two sit-down meals + pastel de nata)
- Attractions: €15–25
- Transport: €5–8
- **Total: ~€135–220/day**

## What to Skip
- Sintra (it's a full separate day, not a half-day)
- Tram 28 (sardine-packed, tourist only)
- Any "fado experience" that hands you a laminated menu at the door

## Stay
**Bairro Alto Hotel** — if budget allows (from €350). Rooftop bar alone justifies it.
**The Independente Hostel & Suites** — converted mansion, doubles from €90, best breakfast in the city.

## Eat Well for Under €15
- Cantina Zé Avillez lunch menu
- Cervejaria Ramiro (lunch only — dinner is a 2hr wait)
- Any Padaria Portuguesa for morning pastry

> Lisbon moves slowly. Build in time to be lost. That's where the blog post actually happens.
